  <data key="d0">Formalin-Ethyl Acetate Sedimentation (FEA-SD) Technique</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A copro-parasitological diagnostic technique used in the pilot survey that, along with qPCR, provided a more accurate diagnosis of Schistosoma japonicum in carabao.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33d09b8957ec6de1ecb70a00240f29b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768504106</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Conventional PCR">
  <data key="d0">Conventional PCR</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A molecular diagnostic technique that recorded a much lower prevalence of Schistosoma japonicum from carabao fecal samples compared to qPCR and FEA-SD.&lt;SEP&gt;Conventional PCR is a diagnostic method that was found to be less sensitive than LAMP for the clinical diagnosis of schistosomiasis cases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33d09b8957ec6de1ecb70a00240f29b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80b97f9e924421f7263d201cc76d061b</data>
