  <data key="d0">Kato-Katz Technique</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A traditional copro-parasitological technique that showed a lower prevalence of Schistosoma japonicum in carabao fecal samples.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnostic technique used as the reference standard for evaluating the performance of immunodiagnostic tests.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnostic technique for which proper application is needed.&lt;SEP&gt;A technique used in a comparison study to detect human Schistosoma japonicum infection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33d09b8957ec6de1ecb70a00240f29b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb64e8269ca7a83eae32849920a5e03b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b11119067a2d2bb4bacfe766355b9408&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63a84e2aacf05868ad446ec5033e575c</data>
