<node id="Bovines">
  <data key="d0">Bovines</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">A broader group of animals, including carabao, whose role in the transmission of Schistosoma japonicum in the Philippines is recognized as more significant than previously thought.&lt;SEP&gt;Bovines are a type of domestic ruminant identified as a major source of Schistosoma japonicum infection, comprising 23.5–58.2% of infected ruminants in the study.&lt;SEP&gt;A category of animals, including water buffaloes, involved in the transmission of S. Japonicum to humans.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33d09b8957ec6de1ecb70a00240f29b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2080ebaf27fa02a0282964a7c0f555bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12418866e7efdfc1aa9ada51674dfa7e</data>
