<node id="Schistosomiasis">
  <data key="d0">Schistosomiasis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Schistosomiasis is the disease caused by infection with Schistosoma japonicum.&lt;SEP&gt;A serious worldwide public health problem.&lt;SEP&gt;Schistosomiasis is a parasitic disease whose control characteristics vary in countries with low parasitic burden and asymptomatic patients.&lt;SEP&gt;A medical condition for which 1107 consecutive cases from Africa were reviewed, diagnosed by microscopy or serology.&lt;SEP&gt;Schistosomiasis is a disease for which CDIFA can be used for rapid screening.&lt;SEP&gt;Schistosomiasis is a parasitic disease whose transmission dynamics are the subject of the study.&lt;SEP&gt;Schistosomiasis is a parasitic disease for which PCR is considered a promising tool for diagnostics and screening.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c33d09b8957ec6de1ecb70a00240f29b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab8696e0621fb10013bbe66408ec389f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0d92923951ea02d5bee6d00bab160af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8934b8f0f1a6ea64c03497182e856f1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6ae8a72ad367bbc353ce113b7956148&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-28ab4980ebe707c8dec2df7bbc3b467d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5176eb820492c017bae55bd3d9afdaaf</data>
