  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Infectious Bursal Disease Virus">
  <data key="d0">Infectious Bursal Disease Virus</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">Infectious Bursal Disease Virus (IBDV) is the causative agent of Infectious Bursal Disease, with various strains circulating in China.&lt;SEP&gt;A virus, specifically three European strains of which were analyzed for their segment A nucleotide sequences.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of virus from which five recent European 'very virulent' isolates were obtained.&lt;SEP&gt;A virus that includes Serotype I, which has different strains described based on their ability to infect cells.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of virus, found in the field in Croatia, represented by the characterized strains Cro-Ig/02, Cro-Po/00, and Cro-Pa/98.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-66b9c03397d1767f2c8fe38e229f4281&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-214b3468d37dada8fb86170176092c52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38be32350c477ea008cc1ed65bb00200&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4599272ede6e40aa9f9d1a217de66bd9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06cfb4b99aa7cb6702274020018749bc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768545705</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Poultry Industry">
  <data key="d0">Poultry Industry</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Poultry Industry is an economic sector whose healthy development is threatened by Infectious Bursal Disease and Novel Variant IBDV.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-66b9c03397d1767f2c8fe38e229f4281</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768506206</data>
