<node id="This Study">
  <data key="d0">This Study</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">This Study is a research effort conducted from 2019 to 2020 to detect IBDV prevalence and analyze genotypes in important poultry-raising areas of China.&lt;SEP&gt;The source of the findings indicating the usefulness of the established iELISA method.&lt;SEP&gt;This study utilizes real-time PCR for the detection and quantification of *C. sinensis* infections.&lt;SEP&gt;The study that demonstrates the effectiveness and achievability of the community-based program for dengue control.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-66b9c03397d1767f2c8fe38e229f4281&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2267b7d403708ba84d848c3e6ebdc424&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe1dcb64ac7b7d66a76a6ee4e711f995&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-155e703201f0d545bdedc2599eaf52a4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768547533</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IBDV Prevalence Data">
  <data key="d0">IBDV Prevalence Data</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">IBDV Prevalence Data indicates that 45.1% (101/224) of samples and 61.9% (26/42) of chicken flocks in China were positive for Infectious Bursal Disease Virus from 2019 to 2020.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-66b9c03397d1767f2c8fe38e229f4281</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768506206</data>
