<node id="Dengue">
  <data key="d0">Dengue</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A disease whose transmission area expansion and diffusion are the subjects of examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Dengue is a systemic viral infection that can be life-threatening for some patients and is transmitted between humans by Aedes mosquitoes.&lt;SEP&gt;Dengue is a disease characterized by specific incidence and severity, identified as a high political priority but facing low resource allocation for prevention and control.&lt;SEP&gt;Dengue is a viral emerging infectious disease that serves as a model for meeting public health challenges in the 21st century.&lt;SEP&gt;The most rapidly advancing vector-borne disease, causing an estimated 50 million infections annually, affecting almost 40% of the world's population, and posing a significant global public health threat.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c492d94e46e6cf3d9b06c416def7bb1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60377a72fdc3717965e736959245d13b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09f7b30a7a44fb488c4648dd1aaa96dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1d9f22d4827e48764fcb87e87f98a6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32039222e39636a5625940ae62b86fb0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1768547194</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
