<node id="100m Sprint Record">
  <data key="d0">100m Sprint Record</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The 100m Sprint Record signifies the fastest officially recorded time for the 100-meter race within the field of athletics. This record functions as a critical benchmark, serving as a significant indicator of elite-level performance and a key measure of speed for sprinters across the globe. It underscores exceptional athletic achievement and reflects remarkable capabilities in the event, establishing itself as a primary standard for athletic performance at this specific race distance.

The current 100m Sprint Record was recently established by Noah Carter, who successfully broke the previous record at the World Athletics Championship. This accomplishment highlights Carter's remarkable speed and performance, solidifying his status within the global athletic community.&lt;SEP&gt;The 100m sprint record is a benchmark in athletics, recently broken by Noah Carter.&lt;SEP&gt;The 100m sprint record was broken by Noah Carter at the World Athletics Championship.</data>
