<node id="VP2">
  <data key="d0">VP2</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">VP2 is a viral protein in which a single amino acid mutation at position 253 can markedly increase the virulence of an attenuated IBDV.&lt;SEP&gt;VP2 is a component of IBDV that contains the determinants for virulence, pathogenic-phenotype markers, and cell tropism.&lt;SEP&gt;A protein encoded by Genomic Segment A of IBDV, in which specific amino acid alterations were made, and which plays a decisive role in IBDV pathogenicity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a24535c690694ea0dca88b58ffad8df3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bd2462ffd61bc9c835e45ba219e87ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8e2acc4aa0c45fe99be141430849f21</data>
