  <data key="d0">Infectious Bursal Disease Virus (IBDV)</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">A virus studied for the influence of its amino acids on adaptation to tissue culture and its pathogenicity.&lt;SEP&gt;Infectious Bursal Disease Virus (IBDV) is a virus with vaccine and wild-type strains whose quasispecies were identified.</data>
