<edge source="100m Sprint Record" target="World Athletics Championship">
  <data key="d7">25.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation (100m Sprint Record, World Athletics Championship) describes a specific athletic event characterized by the breaking of an existing 100-meter sprint record. This signifies the achievement of establishing a new fastest time for the 100-meter sprint.

This notable occurrence explicitly took place during the World Athletics Championship, a prestigious global competition. The championship serves as a prominent venue where athletic records are frequently targeted and often surpassed. Therefore, this relation captures an instance where a previously held 100m sprint record was superseded within the highly competitive environment of the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The 100m sprint record was broken at the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The 100m sprint record was broken at the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The 100m sprint record was broken during the World Athletics Championship.</data>
  <data key="d9">achievement context,achievement location,achievement setting,context,event context,event location,event setting,record achievement,record context,record setting,record-setting,setting</data>
