<edge source="Gold Futures" target="Market Selloff">
  <data key="d7">8.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between Gold Futures and a Market Selloff describes a market dynamic where the value of gold, specifically represented by gold futures and prices, tends to rise. This increase is observed during periods of broader market selloffs.

During such times, investors typically seek safe-haven assets, which are investments perceived as less risky during periods of market volatility or economic uncertainty. Gold is often considered a primary safe-haven asset, leading to increased investor demand and a subsequent upward movement in its price and futures contracts when a market selloff occurs.</data>
  <data key="d9">market reaction,safe-haven investment</data>
