<edge source="Crude Oil" target="Supply Constraints">
  <data key="d7">13.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Crude Oil, Supply Constraints)" describes a consistent market dynamic where limitations or reductions in the availability of crude oil contribute to the support and elevation of its market price. This relationship indicates that when the supply of crude oil is restricted, its price tends to be sustained or increase.

Both historical observations and current market trends demonstrate that supply constraints act as a significant factor in bolstering crude oil prices. This influence is understood to be a fundamental economic principle where scarcity, or the perception of it due to constrained supply, directly impacts the commodity's valuation.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by supply constraints.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by supply constraints.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by supply constraints.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by supply constraints.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by supply constraints.</data>
