<edge source="Crude Oil" target="Strong Demand">
  <data key="d7">13.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation "(Crude Oil, Strong Demand)" describes a fundamental economic principle where robust consumption and industrial need for crude oil provide upward pressure on its market value.

This relationship indicates that when the demand for crude oil is strong, it consistently supports, or contributes to an increase in, crude oil prices. This dynamic has been observed historically and continues to be a prevailing factor in the pricing of crude oil.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.&lt;SEP&gt;Crude oil prices were supported by strong demand.</data>
