<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Analysts">
  <data key="d7">13.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation (Analysts, Market Selloff) describes how market analysts identify and assign causes to a market selloff. In this context, analysts consistently attribute the occurrence of a market selloff to investor concerns.

These concerns are often further characterized as being either specific in nature, pointing to particular identified issues, or various, encompassing a broader range of factors that collectively contribute to the market downturn.&lt;SEP&gt;Analysts attribute the market selloff to various investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;Analysts attribute the market selloff to various investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;Analysts attribute the market selloff to investor concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;Analysts attribute the market selloff to specific factors.&lt;SEP&gt;Analysts attribute the market selloff to investor concerns.</data>
