<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Investor Concerns">
  <data key="d7">11.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between Investor Concerns and Market Selloff signifies that investor concerns are widely attributed as a primary cause for a market selloff. These concerns are identified as a significant factor leading to such market downturns.

Specifically, investor concerns encompassing factors like rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty have been cited as direct drivers contributing to the market selloff. This indicates a causal link where anxieties among investors about various economic and policy-related issues prompt widespread selling activity in the market.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are the attributed cause of the market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are identified as a cause of the market selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;The market selloff is attributed to investor concerns.</data>
