  <data key="d8">The relation "(Market Selloff, Tech Giants)" describes a dynamic where significant declines experienced by tech giants directly contributed to a broader market selloff. This indicates that the substantial drops in the stock values of major technology companies were a key factor in driving or exacerbating a widespread downturn across the market. These significant declines in tech giants' stocks played a pivotal role in the overall market's negative performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Tech giants saw significant declines, contributing to the overall market selloff.</data>
