<edge source="Regulatory Uncertainty" target="Investor Concerns">
  <data key="d7">12.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between Investor Concerns and Regulatory Uncertainty signifies that investor anxieties are frequently centered on the unpredictability of regulations. Regulatory uncertainty is a significant factor that contributes to, drives, and heightens investor concerns. This uncertainty is often recognized as a primary investor concern, playing a role in market downturns, such as contributing to a selloff.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are linked to regulatory uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are over regulatory uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are also over regulatory uncertainty.&lt;SEP&gt;Investor concerns are over regulatory uncertainty.</data>
  <data key="d9">causation,cause,components,concern,driving factor,economic factor,economic impact,effect,factor,factors,financial factors,financial worry,focus,influence,market concern,market sentiment,reason,related to,underlying factor</data>
